                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Key Insights</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Churn rate: 26.58%</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Month-to-month contracts have highest churn (~43%)</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Fiber optic customers churn more than DSL users</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Electronic check users show highest churn risk</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Customers with 0–12 months tenure are most likely to leave</run>
                  <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                  <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>• Churned customers have higher monthly charges</run>
                </formatted-text>
